    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi! In current Neovim nightly, both 0.12 and now 0.13, `:restart` isn't working properly anymore. Neovim does restart, but it does not load any plugins after that. A normal fresh start works, only `:restart` seems broken. It worked a couple of weeks ago.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```bash\nnvim # with stuff in init.lua\n:restart\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nConfiguration is loaded after `:restart` but only a clean nvim window is loaded\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-13+g92a667c07f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ndoesn't matter I guess\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
